</ptxt>
<servinfosub id = "AENBP70A1306022001" page = "2">
<title>
IAT Sensor Inspection
</title>
<attention4>
<ptxt>
The MAF and IAT sensor will be damaged if exposed to a temperature higher than 100 &#176;C (212 &#176;F).
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Do not heat the MAF and IAT sensor to a temperature higher than 100 &#176;C (212 &#176;F).
</ptxt>
</attention4>
<s1 page = "2">
<ptxt>
Remove MAF and IAT sensor. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A1306021"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1 page = "2">
<ptxt>
Check MAF and IAT sensor O-ring (1) for damage and deterioration. Replace if necessary.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1 page = "2">
<ptxt>
Check that resistance between sensor terminals varies depending on temperature while blowing hot air to temperature sensing part (2) of MAF and IAT sensor (3) using a hair dryer (4).
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
If faulty condition is found, replace MAF and IAT sensor. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A1306021"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
<c-change/>
